President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Oklahoma and authorized federal aid to assist in recovery efforts from a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred in January and February 2011. The funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs, and replacement in various counties. Additionally, assistance for emergency protective measures and snow assistance will be provided for a specific period of time in certain counties. Federal funding for hazard mitigation measures statewide is also available. William J. Doran III has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA.